üìã Basic S3 Commands:

| Action                               | Command                                 | Example                              |
| ------------------------------------ | --------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| ü™£ List all buckets                  | `aws s3 ls`                             | ‚Äî                                    |
| üìÇ List files in a bucket            | `aws s3 ls s3://my-bucket`              | `aws s3 ls s3://project-data`        |
| üÜï Create a new bucket               | `aws s3 mb s3://my-bucket-name`         | `aws s3 mb s3://new-demo-bucket`     |
| üóëÔ∏è Delete a bucket                  | `aws s3 rb s3://my-bucket-name`         | `aws s3 rb s3://old-bucket`          |
| üóëÔ∏è Delete a bucket (with all files) | `aws s3 rb s3://my-bucket-name --force` | `aws s3 rb s3://test-bucket --force` |

üì¶ Working with Objects (Files):

Action	Command	Example: 

| Action             | Command                                    | Example                                    |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------ |
| ‚¨ÜÔ∏è Upload a file   | `aws s3 cp file.txt s3://my-bucket/`       | `aws s3 cp report.pdf s3://docs-bucket/`   |
| ‚¨áÔ∏è Download a file | `aws s3 cp s3://my-bucket/file.txt .`      | `aws s3 cp s3://docs-bucket/report.pdf .`  |
| üîÅ Sync folders    | `aws s3 sync local-folder s3://my-bucket/` | `aws s3 sync ./backup s3://backup-bucket/` |
| ‚ùå Delete a file    | `aws s3 rm s3://my-bucket/file.txt`        | `aws s3 rm s3://project/file.txt`          |

